HEADWORD: Hobble skirt
<hw>Hob"ble skirt</hw>. <def>A woman's skirt so scant at the bottom as
to restrain freedom of movement after the fashion of a hobble.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Hob"ble-skirt`ed</wf>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hobblingly</ent>⟦br⟧
